	<p>Why do so many truly great products remain unknown to the world?</p>

	<p>Here, there is a shapewear brand that customers have sought out for 20 years without any sustained advertising. Here, there is a toothbrush and toothpaste that, once used, people say they cannot live without—and they have been using it for 10, 20 years. How did these incredible products survive for decades? And why don't most consumers know this fact?</p>

